Politico-economic Influences

I say now that people struggle to show love because their life is difficult. When I continue to break it down to an actionable stage I find, at the heart of it, ineffectual politico-economic systems. 

Why did the world let itself adopt Neoliberal systems of thought? Trickle-down economics doesn't work. Why did people let this happen? What can I do? Should I continue to engage with this and learn or continue with school? It seems that I want to look big picture, but perhaps it's possible that I stay zoomed out that I don't ever get anything actionable done...
